    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "This hadith provides Ibn Abbas's exegesis of Quran 7:143, which describes Moses recovering after asking to see God and the mountain crumbling. According to Ibn Abbas, Moses's repentance was specifically for requesting to see God, and his declaration of being 'the first of the believers' meant he was the first to affirm the impossibility of seeing God. This interpretation supports the theological position that God is beyond physical vision, a view central to many Islamic theological schools.",
